07/02/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Launching negotiations on a Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU marks the beginning of an irreversible process of integration, says Prime Minister Fatos Nano. 
Assessing the work of the government over the past six months, Nano on Thursday (6 February) described the negotiations as an opportunity for Albania to "to work intensively with Brussels and governments of the region, to accelerate reforms." He stressed that political, economic and institutional stability are important prerequisites for membership, along with integration into regional markets and judicial and security reforms. 
(Albanian News - 07/02/03; ATA - 06/02/03)
